# Melina · the kindling maiden with the burned eye

Melina appears at the start of the Tarnished's journey as a mysterious maiden offering an accord: she will turn runes to strength and lend her ring that summons a horse, and in return asks only to be taken to the foot of the Erdtree. She is bodiless, born within the Erdtree itself, with one eye sealed — a figure half present in the world she guides her champion through.

Her purpose was long ago burned into her, and it is a purpose of sacrifice. At the foot of the Erdtree she gives herself as kindling to ignite the Flame of Ruin, opening the way forward at the cost of her own existence. She does not waver from this; she was, in her own framing, built to burn.

There is one fracture in the accord. If the Tarnished takes the Frenzied Flame instead, Melina's gentleness turns to a vow: she will deliver Destined Death against them. The same resolve that carries her to the kindling carries her to that promise.

Her emergence is spiritual because she is sacrifice made person — a being whose whole existence is an act of faith and self-offering in service of the journey to the Erdtree, grace given form and then given to the fire.
